# Root Cause First

When fixing bugs, prioritize removing the actual source of bad behavior instead of adding broad defensive code paths.

- Prefer minimal, direct fixes at the origin of the issue (parser, transformer, data write path, or core logic).
- Avoid fallback/normalization patches in downstream UI/controller layers unless explicitly requested.
- Add defensive code only when the root cause cannot be fixed safely now, and explain why in the final response.
- If temporary defensive code is required, keep it narrow and create a follow-up task to remove it after root-cause fix lands.

